The '''Dominican Adventist University''' (in Spanish : '''Universidad Adventista Dominicana (UNAD)''') is a [[university]] owned by the [[Seventh-day Adventist Church]], in [[Santo Domingo]] in the [[Dominican Republic]].
==History== The Dominican Adventist University found its origins in the Dominican Adventist College, established in 1947, which remained open until 1992, in the Herrera quarter.<ref>{{es}} {{cite web |title=Dominican Adventist University, history |url=http://universidadadventistadominicana.blogspot.com/2009/03/historia.html |publisher=''Universidad Adventista Dominicana'' |accessdate=2009-06-30}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>
In 2007, the university had 1,143 students and 105 teachers.<ref>{{fr}} {{cite web |title=RÃ©publique Dominicaine |url=http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/article_imprim.php3?id_article=14767 |publisher=''Diplomatie Gouvernement FranÃ§ais'' |accessdate=2009-06-30}}</ref>
